Playwright Locator Cheat Sheet (Copy-Paste Text Version)

Why use these locators?
	•	They are stable, auto-waiting, and reduce flakiness.
	•	They are better than XPath and CSS in most cases.

⸻

	1.	getByRole()  — Based on ARIA roles

⸻

Use when elements have semantic meaning (buttons, links, textboxes, headings, etc.)

Examples:
page.getByRole(‘button’, { name: ‘Login’ }).click();
page.getByRole(‘textbox’, { name: ‘Email’ }).fill(‘user@test.com’);
page.getByRole(‘link’, { name: ‘Home’ }).click();
page.getByRole(‘heading’, { level: 1 }).isVisible();

Example HTML:
Submit

Locator:
page.getByRole(‘button’, { name: ‘Submit’ }).click();

⸻

	2.	getByLabel() — Input fields tied to a 

⸻

Examples:
page.getByLabel(‘Username’).fill(‘john’);
page.getByLabel(‘Password’).fill(‘Welcome@123’);
page.getByLabel(‘Remember me’).check();

Example HTML:
Email Address


Locator:
page.getByLabel(‘Email Address’).fill(‘test@gmail.com’);

⸻

	3.	getByPlaceholder() — For placeholder-based inputs

⸻

Examples:
page.getByPlaceholder(‘Search here…’).fill(‘Playwright’);
page.getByPlaceholder(‘Enter email’).fill(‘user@test.com’);

⸻

	4.	getByText() — Match visible text on screen

⸻

Examples:
page.getByText(‘Order Summary’).click();
expect(page.getByText(‘Payment Successful’)).toBeVisible();

Supports regex:
page.getByText(/Success/i).isVisible();

⸻

	5.	getByTestId() — Best for stable tests (if app has test IDs)

⸻

HTML:
Add

Locator:
page.getByTestId(‘add-to-cart’).click();

Recommend: Ask developers to add test IDs in new UI screens.

⸻

	6.	locator() — Generic locator using CSS or XPath

⸻

Examples:
const price = page.locator(’.price-value’);
price.first().click();

CSS examples:
page.locator(’#login-btn’).click();
page.locator(’[type=“submit”]’).click();

XPath (use only if needed):
page.locator(’//table//tr’).nth(2).click();

⸻

	7.	Locators with Filters

⸻

Examples:
page.getByRole(‘button’).filter({ hasText: ‘Save’ }).click();
page.locator(‘div’).filter({ has: page.getByText(‘Account’) }).click();
page.getByRole(‘listitem’).nth(2).click(); // selects 3rd element

⸻

Handling Dropdown Without 

page.getByPlaceholder(‘Search country’).fill(‘India’);
page.getByRole(‘option’, { name: ‘India’ }).click();

⸻

Complete Login Example

import { test, expect } from ‘@playwright/test’;

test(‘Login Test’, async ({ page }) => {
await page.goto(‘https://example.com/login’);

await page.getByLabel(‘Email’).fill(‘test@gmail.com’);
await page.getByLabel(‘Password’).fill(‘Test@123’);
await page.getByRole(‘button’, { name: ‘Sign In’ }).click();

await expect(page.getByText(‘Welcome’)).toBeVisible();
});

⸻

Summary Locator Table

getByRole()      → For buttons, textboxes, headings, links
getByLabel()     → For inputs tied to labels
getByPlaceholder() → For search bars or hint text fields
getByText()      → To click or verify visible text
getByTestId()    → Most stable, recommended for long-term UI testing
locator()        → CSS / XPath fallback locator

